      <originalsloc id="aspace_bdf5229d1d8449d79cf1b847bc35a154">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 222) and in the Bogdan Radica Papers (MS 1588).   The papers consist of official reports, correspondence, subject files, extensive clippings, writings, and printed matter which document Bogdan Radica's work as a press officer in the Yugoslav Legation in Washington, D.C. and the Yugoslav Information Center in New York during World War II. The papers highlight Radica's efforts to inform his government of American press (including the emigre press) coverage of affairs in Yugoslavia and the Balkans, his propagandistic work in support of governmental policies, and his contacts with the Croat, Slovene, and Serb communities in the United States. The papers also illustrate Radica's personal and professional interests in postwar Yugoslavia, including the political activities of the various exile communities.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
